reviews.review_text: Another Great Show from a Great Run I still think the gold-standard for this run at the Music Hall was the first night (9th) but this is an excellent show as well. Strong first set with an excellent Roses. The second set features a run of St. Stephen>Dancing>Music Never Stopped which is out of this world. If anything, 76 was a year when the Dead tapped into some serious grooves and you can definitely sample some of that here. Also, a great Eyes> Stella Blue later in the set.

Sounds like a studio recording Such a delicate touch the band has. This could easily be an album, except for the fact that the Dead's albums are pretty stiff and lack the luster of fluidity. This is loose but precise. Excellent. And one more thing--the other SB has a cut on the audio during Scarlet. This is the best copy.
